# Directory Enumeration Report Using Gobuster

## Objective

The objective of this exercise was to perform directory enumeration against the target web application using Gobuster to identify accessible directories, files, and hidden resources.

## Tools Used

* **Operating System:** Kali Linux
* **Enumeration Tool:** Gobuster v3.8.2
* **Wordlist:** `/usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt`

---

# Test 1: High-Concurrency Scan

## Command Executed

```bash
gobuster dir \
-u http://lab.sigosec.com \
-w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt \
-t 150 \
-o result.txt
```

Figure 1. Gobuster directory enumeration using 150 concurrent threads.

<p align="center"> <img src="https://files.catbox.moe/0f0unf.png" alt="Figure 1. Gobuster directory enumeration output" width="900"> </p>

## Scan Configuration

| Parameter   | Value                    |
| ----------- | ------------------------ |
| Target URL  | `http://lab.sigosec.com` |
| HTTP Method | GET                      |
| Threads     | 150                      |
| Wordlist    | `common.txt`             |
| Timeout     | 10 seconds               |
| Output File | `result.txt`             |

## Findings

The scan completed successfully after testing all **4,750** entries contained in the selected wordlist.

The following paths were discovered:

| Path                                 | HTTP Status | Observation        |
| ------------------------------------ | ----------- | ------------------ |
| `/.git/logs/`                        | 308         | Permanent Redirect |
| `/cgi-bin/`                          | 308         | Permanent Redirect |
| `/render?url=https://www.google.com` | 308         | Permanent Redirect |
| `/render/https://www.google.com`     | 308         | Permanent Redirect |

Several timeout errors were encountered during the scan. Some examples include:

* `Browser`
* `bin`
* `cachemgr.cgi`

These timeout messages indicate that the target server did not respond within the configured timeout period for some requests.

